        <h1><marquee behavior="alternate" ;bgcolor="lightblue";height="1000">Garlic Butter Lobster Tails</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>4 lobster tails, thawed if frozen</li>
            <li>1/2 cup unsalted butter, melted</li>
            <li>4 cloves garlic, minced</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons fresh lemon juice</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon paprika</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon salt</li>
            <li>1/4 teaspoon black pepper</li>
            <li>Chopped fresh parsley for garnish</li>
            <li>Lemon wedges for serving</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>seafood</li>
            <li>indian</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Preheat the oven to 425°F (220°C).</li>
            <li>Using kitchen shears, cut through the top shell of the lobster tails, stopping at the base of the tail. Do not cut through the bottom shell.</li>
            <li>Gently lift the lobster meat from the shell, keeping it attached at the base.</li>
            <li>In a small bowl, combine melted butter, minced garlic, lemon juice, paprika, salt, and black pepper.</li>
            <li>Place the lobster tails on a baking sheet or in a baking dish. Brush the lobster meat with the garlic butter mixture.</li>
            <li>Bake in the preheated oven for 12-15 minutes or until the lobster meat is opaque and the shells are bright red.</li>
            <li>Remove from the oven and garnish with chopped fresh parsley.</li>
            <li>Serve hot with lemon wedges on the side.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your indulgent Garlic Butter Lobster Tails!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>
